  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Meals at Lac Salin are not just your average bite to eat, a lot of time and effort goes into the menu and sourcing the best quality ingredients, much of which is sourced locally. The hotel also keeps the wine cellar stocked up with a wide range of bottles from all around the globe.  </p>
<p>Start the day with a a cup of freshly brewed coffee or a pot of herbal tea to accompany the great selection up at the buffet table. Expect fresh breads, jams, local mountain butter, cheeses and meats. You'll also find fruit, juices and fresh eggs.</p>
<p>Dinner is really where the restaurant comes to life. You shouldn't go hungry with four delicious courses to work your way through. We particularly enjoyed the selection of deserts across the buffet table, the perfect way to finish a meal. </p>
<p>This season the hotel has opened the resorts first vegetarian and vegan restaurant, focus on local produce and really tantalising the tastebuds and taking you on an experience like never before. </p>]]></cateringDescription>
